<subSubSection id="ABD355A0FFD3FFE2FC8AB6FBFE2E07CD" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="E376062BFFD3FFE2FC8AB6FBFDE8066D" blockId="1.[810,1450,2045,2100]" lastBlockId="2.[135,773,189,596]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD3FFE1FC8AB6FBFAE00C2D" authority="Bleeker, 1860 c" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[810,1285,2045,2069]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Cheilodipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polystigma">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD3FFE1FC8AB6FBFBAA0C2C" box="[810,1103,2046,2069]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Cheilodipterus polystigma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD3FFE1FBF9B6F8FAE00C2D" author="Bleeker, P" box="[1113,1285,2045,2068]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" pagination="446 - 456" refId="ref6399" refString="Bleeker, P., 1860 c. Derde bijdrage tot de kennis der vischfauna van Singapoera. Natuurkundig Tijdschrift voor Nederlandsche- Indie, 20: 446 - 456." type="journal article" year="1860">Bleeker, 1860c</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is based on a coloured painting by Castelnau, No. 137 (Fig. 3). Bleeker provided a brief description in Dutch based on this painting. In his revision of the 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FEE1B1D8FE2604CD" box="[321,451,221,244]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Apogonidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD0FFE2FE6BB1D8FD9D04CD" author="Bleeker, P" box="[459,632,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref6599" refString="Bleeker, P., 1874. Revision des especes Indo-Archipelagiques du groupe des Apogonini. Natuurkundige Verhandelingen der Hollandsche Maatschappij der Wetenschappen, Series 2, 3 (1): 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="1874">Bleeker’s (1874)</bibRefCitation>
redescription in Latin of this species was based on 
<specimenCount id="F5CFCDA2FFD0FFE2FD8CB1F8FD35052D" box="[556,720,253,276]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
, one from 
<collectingCountry id="9BDE46BBFFD0FFE2FF62B018FECB050D" box="[194,302,285,308]" name="Singapore" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Singapore</collectingCountry>
(collected during a ten day stopover on his return to Europe in 1860) and the other from 
<collectingCountry id="9BDE46BBFFD0FFE2FDF7B038FD42056D" box="[599,679,317,340]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Ambon</collectingCountry>
(RMNH 5610). Bleeker’s translated remarks (1874) are as follows: “Rem. I described this species for the first time in the year 1859 according to a drawing of Mr. the Count de Castelnau. At the time of my passage to 
<collectingCountry id="9BDE46BBFFD0FFE2FE6FB0B8FDDB05ED" box="[463,574,445,468]" name="Singapore" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, in the year 1860, I obtained a beautiful specimen, and I also have a smaller specimen, poorly preserved from 
<collectingCountry id="9BDE46BBFFD0FFE2FE5EB0F8FDB7062D" box="[510,594,509,532]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Ambon</collectingCountry>
. One easily can identify the species by the eye-like black mark offset dorsally on the side of the caudal peduncle”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E376062BFFD0FFE2FF27B378FE2E07CD" blockId="2.[135,772,637,1012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD0FFE2FF27B378FEBD06AD" author="Randall, J" box="[135,344,637,660]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref8184" refString="Randall, J. E., E. A. Lachner, &amp; T. H. Fraser, 1985. A revision of the Indo-Pacific apogonid fish genus Pseudamia with descriptions of three new species. Indo-Pacific Fishes, 6: 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1985">Randall et al. (1985)</bibRefCitation>
mention these specimens in their material list of 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FF68B39BFD6B068D" authority="(Bleeker, 1856)" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[200,654,669,693]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amblyuroptera">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD0FFE2FF68B39BFE07068C" box="[200,482,670,693]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Pseudamia amblyuroptera</emphasis>
(Bleeker, 1856)
</taxonomicName>
but did not identify either of them as a possible 
<typeStatus id="3C72B889FFD0FFE2FD83B3B8FD9F06ED" box="[547,634,701,724]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">syntype</typeStatus>
. Castelnau’s painting is the representation of the type specimen, lost or possibly yet to be located among the preserved/dried material at the ZMUL. As both the 
<collectingCountry id="9BDE46BBFFD0FFE2FE31B218FE1F070D" box="[401,506,797,820]" name="Singapore" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Singapore</collectingCountry>
specimen and the 
<collectingCountry id="9BDE46BBFFD0FFE2FD15B218FCE1070D" box="[693,772,797,820]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Ambon</collectingCountry>
specimen apparently were obtained after Bleeker’s original description of 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FE84B25BFE5F074C" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[292,442,862,885]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Cheilodipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polystigma">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD0FFE2FE84B25BFE5F074C" box="[292,442,862,885]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">C. polystigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published, neither can be regarded as types. In their remarks, 
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD0FFE2FDBDB278FCE107AD" author="Randall, J" box="[541,772,893,916]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref8184" refString="Randall, J. E., E. A. Lachner, &amp; T. H. Fraser, 1985. A revision of the Indo-Pacific apogonid fish genus Pseudamia with descriptions of three new species. Indo-Pacific Fishes, 6: 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1985">Randall et al. (1985)</bibRefCitation>
discuss their reasons why 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FE01B29BFD71078C" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker, 1859-" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[417,660,926,949]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polystigma">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD0FFE2FE01B29BFD71078C" box="[417,660,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Pseudamia polystigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FE00B2BBFDBF07EC" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[416,602,958,981]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amblyuroptera">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD0FFE2FE00B2BBFDBF07EC" box="[416,602,958,981]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">P. amblyuroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the result of variation associated with size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ABD355A0FFD0FFE2FF27B518FD3200ED" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" type="description">
<paragraph id="E376062BFFD0FFE2FF27B518FD3200ED" blockId="2.[135,773,1053,1237]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
The coloured painting can be easily identified with the species treated by 
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD0FFE2FF57B538FE37006D" author="Randall, J" box="[247,466,1085,1108]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref8184" refString="Randall, J. E., E. A. Lachner, &amp; T. H. Fraser, 1985. A revision of the Indo-Pacific apogonid fish genus Pseudamia with descriptions of three new species. Indo-Pacific Fishes, 6: 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1985">Randall et al. (1985)</bibRefCitation>
and with Bleeker’s figure of 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FF27B55BFE79004C" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[135,412,1118,1141]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Cheilodipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polystigma">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD0FFE2FF27B55BFE79004C" box="[135,412,1118,1141]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Cheilodipterus polystigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD0FFE2FE08B558FDD8004D" author="Bleeker, P" box="[424,573,1117,1140]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 156" refId="ref6635" refString="Bleeker, P., 1875 - 76. Atlas ichthyologique des Indes Orientales Neerlandaises, publie sous les auspices du Gouvernement colonial neerlandais. Percoides II, (Spariformes), Bogodoides, Cirrhiteoides. Atlas ichthyologique des Indes Orientales Neerlandaises, publie sous les auspices du Gouvernement colonial neerlandais. Tome VIII: 1 - 156." type="book chapter" year="1875">Bleeker, 1875</bibRefCitation>
– 
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD0FFE2FDECB558FD66004D" author="Bleeker, P" box="[588,643,1117,1140]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="138 - 148" refId="ref6694" refString="Bleeker, P., 1876. Description de quelques especes insulindiennes inedites des genres Oxyurichthys, Paroxyurichthys et Cryptocentrus. Verslagen en Mededeelingen der Koninklijke Akademie van Wetenschappen. Afdeling Natuurkunde Amsterdam, Series. 2, 9: 138 - 148." type="journal article" year="1876">1876</bibRefCitation>
: Pl. 70). The figure of 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FF44B57BFE1C00AC" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[228,505,1150,1173]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amblyuroptera">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD0FFE2FF44B57BFE1C00AC" box="[228,505,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Pseudamia amblyuroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD0FFE2FDA6B578FD7F00AD" author="Bleeker, P" box="[518,666,1149,1172]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref6538" refString="Bleeker, P., 1871 - 76. Atlas ichthyologique des Indes Orientales Neerlandaises, publie sous les auspices du Gouvernement colonial neerlandais. Percoides I, Priacanthiformes, Serraniformes, Grammisteiformes, Percaeformes, Datniaeformes. Atlas ichthyologique des Indes Orientales Neerlandaises, publie sous les auspices du Gouvernement colonial neerlandais. Tome VII: 1 - 126." type="book chapter" year="1871">Bleeker, 1871</bibRefCitation>
– 
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD0FFE2FD08B578FD3A00AD" author="Bleeker, P" box="[680,735,1149,1172]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="138 - 148" refId="ref6694" refString="Bleeker, P., 1876. Description de quelques especes insulindiennes inedites des genres Oxyurichthys, Paroxyurichthys et Cryptocentrus. Verslagen en Mededeelingen der Koninklijke Akademie van Wetenschappen. Afdeling Natuurkunde Amsterdam, Series. 2, 9: 138 - 148." type="journal article" year="1876">1876</bibRefCitation>
: Pl. 32) appears more diagrammatic. We agree that 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FD2EB59BFEC000EC" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1856" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amblyuroptera">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD0FFE2FD2EB59BFEC000EC" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Pseudamia amblyuroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD0FFE2FDE0B5BBFD3500EC" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[576,720,1214,1237]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Cheilodipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polystigma">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD0FFE2FDE0B5BBFD3500EC" box="[576,720,1214,1237]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">P. polystigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
